<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A very local and range-restricted species, previously known from the Greek and the Bulgarian sides of Mt. Orvilos (also known as Ali 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Botuš">Botus</normalizedToken>
), although 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, J. R. I." journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1 - 282" refId="B7670178" refString="Wood, J. R.I., Williams, B. R.M., Mitchell, T. C., Carine, M. A., Harris, D. J., Scotland, R. W., 2015. A foundation monograph of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae). PhytoKeys 51: 1 - 282" title="A foundation monograph of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae)" volume="51" year="2015">Wood et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
omit Greece in the distribution range of the species. Specimens from Mt. Slavjanka, Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, J. R. I." journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1 - 282" refId="B7670178" refString="Wood, J. R.I., Williams, B. R.M., Mitchell, T. C., Carine, M. A., Harris, D. J., Scotland, R. W., 2015. A foundation monograph of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae). PhytoKeys 51: 1 - 282" title="A foundation monograph of Convolvulus L. (Convolvulaceae)" volume="51" year="2015">Wood et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and observations from Mt. Angistro, Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, K." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 26 (3): 537 - 572" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7670041" refString="Tan, K., Kofinas, G., 2020. New floristic records in the Balkans: 43. Phytologia Balcanica, 26 (3): 537-572" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 43" year="2020">Tan and Kofinas 2020</bibRefCitation>
) slightly extended the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
area of occurrence. The new locality on Mt. Achladovouno (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F7677649" captionText="Figure 16. Convolvulus suendermannii from Mt. Achladovouno (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640555" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">16</figureCitation>
), ca. 100 km to the SE of Orvilos, is isolated and forms the easternmost border in the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
distribution (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F7677669" captionText="Figure 17. Distribution map of Convolvulus suendermannii, Lomelosia rhodopensis, Drymocallis rupestris and Saxifraga pedemontana subsp. cymosa in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656581" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">17</figureCitation>
). It was not found together with either 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. lineatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">C. lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. or 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. boissieri subsp. compactus" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="subSpecies" species="boissieri" subSpecies="compactus">C. boissieri subsp. compactus</taxonomicName>
(Boiss.) Stace, the presumed parents of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. suendermannii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="suendermannii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">C. suendermannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in case the hybridogenous origin is hypothesised.
</paragraph>
